1️⃣ Create VM Instance

Go to Compute Engine → VM Instances → Create Instance.

OS: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS

Machine type: e2-micro (free-tier eligible)

Choose nearest region for better performance.

2️⃣ Configure Firewall

Enable HTTP and HTTPS traffic.

3️⃣ Launch Instance

Click Create and wait until it’s running.

Note the External IP.

4️⃣ Connect via SSH

Click SSH → Open in Browser Window.

A terminal window opens — your remote Linux VM.

5️⃣ Test Connection
Run basic commands:

uname -a
ls
whoami


6️⃣ Stop or Delete When Done

From the dashboard, Stop or Delete the instance to save credits
